    <stitle>CF 500, CF 600 Suspension - Front Suspension - General Procedures</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="6">
        <title>General Procedures</title>
        <svcsubproc id="x204011101">
            <title>Wheel Bearing Adjustment</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>New wheel seals on the front axles must be installed any time the axle lubricants are changed
                        from factory-installed mineral lube to synthetic lube or vice versa.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>If bearings are adjusted too tightly, they will overheat and wear rapidly. An adjustment that
                        is excessively loose can cause pounding and contribute to uneven tire wear, steering
                        difficulties and inefficient brakes. Check bearing adjustment at regular inspection intervals.
                        New wheel seals must be installed when the hub is removed. A damaged or worn seal can permit
                        bearing lubricant to reach the brake linings, resulting in ineffective brake operation and
                        necessitating premature replacement of linings.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>To check the wheel bearing adjustment, raise the front of the vehicle. Grasp the tire at the
                        sides, and alternately push inward and pull outward on the tire. If any looseness is felt,
                        adjust the front wheel bearings as follows.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the hub cap and gasket from the hub.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0401002" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0020767.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove and discard the cotter pin.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0401003" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figdf1/Df1219b.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="208px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">While rotating the wheel, tighten the wheel bearing adjusting nut to 271 Nm (200 lbf-ft)
                    to seat the bearings.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0401004" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0020737.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="208px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Back off the wheel bearing adjusting nut one full turn.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">While rotating the wheel, tighten the wheel bearing adjusting nut to 68 Nm (50 lb-in).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen the wheel bearing adjusting nut 1/4 turn to achieve final bearing adjustment end
                    play.
                </para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>Final bearing adjustment end play must be within the specification.</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>The final adjustment must not result in a preloaded bearing.</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0401005" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0024618.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If the cotter pin hole lines up with a slot in the nut, install a new cotter pin. If it
                    does not, loosen the adjusting nut to align a slot with the first available cotter pin hole. Install
                    a new cotter pin.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0401006" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figdf1/Df1219b.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="208px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the gasket and hub cap.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0401007" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0020767.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
